						               													<description>Dust to Dust is a competitive deckbuilding and disintegration game set in a reclaimed world.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the game, you grew up on an Island in the sky. But they didn&amp;rsquo;t tell you it was falling into the gene-splicing black sand of the Dust until you became a Diver. Now you race other Divers through the Dust itself, retrieving all the fusion shards you can to be the one who restores your Island to the sky.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To win, you&amp;rsquo;ll need help from allies recruited from the creatures who still dwell on Urth, like the plant-animal hybrid Biofauna, the newly sentient Machina, or the fearsome remains of humanity called the Colony.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Gameplay&amp;#10;Players draft cards from a market by purchasing them with starting energy coin cards&amp;#10;Players play actions (Allies) from their hand after adding them to their decks, leading to combos&amp;#10;Players also interact with each other by attacking or defending with their actions (Allies)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When the Final Race is triggered, each player takes one more turn, besides the player who triggered it. Fusion Shards are then counted up by each player according to diamond icons on their Relics, Fusion Fragments, and Allies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is the Diver who accumulates the most fusion shards across their acquired Relics, Fusion Fragments, and Allies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
